column5: sure there's always one in every crowd.....LOL
17 lookers so far. LOL Lets see how many I can get.
I was going to blast you along with everyone else lol  I think all the bass fisherman have had enough of this winter stuff hehe  Tony
Sure Brian....you drive...I know a nice spot on Cassels Lake in Temagami...
Who needs to drive when you have friends with wings.LOL  125 and counting.  Im not as dumb as some think ya know.LOL
OK OK< enough already!  LOL  Jen

Brian...you think a sled in the slush is no fun...not into it with an airplane what so ever...   And BTW...you didn't specify the lake you wanted to go to.... so... well...maybe people thought you were headin North where Trout are open right thru 'till Sept 30th (except Lake Temagami)
You mean travel when everything is right here.
I took the bait, now set the hook!    (what a cruel thing to do to a newbie, looking for a first ice fishing experience)
BBOG,Theres lots of ice drill,n and perch,n and pike,n to do still.Just be safe out there.  A few of us will be pike,n sunday if yer interested. There will be hooters.
You, Brian, are a bugger.  I thought you were heading north and genuine in your offering.
hahaha... nice!  I was suckered too...
Ill bet Lake Joe still has some ice ... ya had me ready to say OK !!!!
